{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_brookland_ver01/data/sn84026749/00205696398/1930102501/0225.xml":{"full_text":"THE WEATHER\nFair and slightly colder tonight; minimum\ntemperature about 30 degrees. Sunday fair,\nmoderate northwest and north winds. Tempera\nture yesterday\u2014Highest, 52; lowest, 42.\nFull Wnthtr Report on Page IS\nThs Washington Times Is the only afternoon paper In\nthia city publishing the news dispatches of International\nNews Service and Universal Service.\nCOLLINS RIDICULES DEFENSE GUN TESTS\nGangs Claim Another\nt ii\u00dft M\n.X\nm\nK\nJE Bk w BL t. -k\nMSMSmt JMBfe\nA[f M 'T\nAs F I I\nJF -fj\nUli\ns 4s IE\nbl I\nB\nomhk joaseseaM*\u00ab\nMRS. AIELLO\nNATION SPEEDS\u2019\nJOBLESS HID\nThe nation-wide response to the\ncall for unemployment relief has\nbeen instantaneous, constructive\nand highly satisfactory. Col.\nArthur Woods, Federal employ\nment administrator, announced\nthis afternoon.\nIn the past 48 hours, he said,\nliterally thousands of telegrams\nand letters have poured into his\nheadquarters here from business,\nIndustrial and charity leaders\npledging their* co-operation in the\nGovernment\u2019s campaign to relieve\nthe stringency of present condi\ntions.\nA campaign to have industry\npledge that no employes will be\nreleased until the unemployment'\ncrisis is past, is under considera\ntion by the President\u2019s committee.\nThe appointment of Frederick\nC. Croxton, of Columbus, Ohio,\nas regional director for the Mid\ndle West, is a forerunner of the\nappointment of others. The or\nganization probably will be car\nried further by the appointment\nof press agents to work under the\nregional directors.\nNo job will be too small to be\nacceptable. If the housewives of\nthe country can be enlisted to\ngive a day\u2019s work here and there,\nthat will help in the emergency,\nit was said. Every agency, large\nand small, that can give work is\nasked to do so.\nOne measure of relief, from\n\u25a0which Colonel Woods expects far\nreaching results, is the approval\nby the voters of many States No\nvember 4, of bond issues totaling\n$450,000,000.\nNEW YORK, Oct. 25 (1.N.5.).\nActual work of providing food,\nclothes, coal and housing to the\nunemployed here will start as\nsoon as the work of counting the\nunemployed and homeless is\ncompleted by police. It will be i\nfinanced by contributions as well\nas by city funds.\nSlash \u201cRed Tape\u201d to Aid\nJobless, Glenn Urges\nCongressional demands that the\nGovernment slash \u201cred tape\u201d to\nspeed public building are being\nserved on the Administration ac\ncompanied by declarations that\npreliminary activities are so in\nvolved that there can not be ade-\nquate expansion to greatly relieve\nthe employment situation.\nSenator Otis F. Glenn R> of\nIllinois has formally requested\nSecretary of Commerce Lamont\nand Postmaster General Brown to\ntake action to this end.\nIn The Times Today\nPage\nChurch Pa-e 7\nComics 1\"\nDrama''!\u201d\u2019*! 5, 6\nFinancial F\u2019j\u2019-s r., s, 13\nMagazine Page 11\nRadio 20\nSociety 8\nSports 9, 10, 11\nHr W\nEM\nw j\n1\n\u2014lnternational Newsreel\nJOE AIELLO\nAIELLO, ri\u2019/al of Al Capone,\nwas mowed down by gang\nbullets in Chicago. His widow\nwas subjected to a severe\ngrilling in an effort to obtain\nsome clue. Her son. Carl, tries\nto console the collapsing widow\nas she is questioned by State\u2019s\nAttorney Abraham Marowitz\n(Story on Page 15)\nTffITZDNES\nSTANDARDIZED\nConfusion in the minds of\npatrons of the flat-rate cabs .in\nWashington as to how far they\ncan ride without having to pay in\ncreased fare will be eliminated by\na plan adopted today by six of the\nleading cab companies of the city.\nAfter a series of conferences be\ntween the heads of the leading\nwhite and colored cab concerns\nand Richmond Keech, People\u2019s\nCounsel, before the Public Utili\nties Commission, a standardized\nzoning of the city has been agreed\nupon and maps showing the va\nrious zones have been printed. It\nis planned to post these maps\nconspicuously in every cao oper\nated by the agreeing companies,\nso that passengers may see just\nhow far their fare will take them.\nThe city has been divided into\nfour zones. The first, embracing\nthe principal business section of\nthe District, is designated as the\n35 cent zone, and an additional\n25 cents is charged for each zone\nin addition to the first. The\nfourth\n?!*ins section only.\nIt is brought o it that, as long\n?s a cab remains wit\u2019iln the zone\nwhere it picks up a fare, the first\nzone rate is charged. As soon\nas it crosses into another zone,\nhowever, the rate increases to 60\ncents, and crossing the next\nzone line again increMM the tare.\nWASHTB\u00bbTIMES\nI NQ -15,376\nClergy Indorses \u201cBuy Now\u201d Campaign\nPLOT TO KILL KING CAROL FOILED\nCAMPBELL GUN\nTESTS AROUSE\nLAWYERS\nCollins Rejects As \u201cAsinine\u201d\nProposal of the Defense;\nConference Only Solution\nAssistant United States At\ntorney Willia mH. Collins today\nbranded as \u201casinine\u201d a counter\nproposal of the attorneys of Her\nbert M. Campbell, on trial here,\naccused of slaying Mary Baker,\nApril 11. and emphatically de\nclared that his intention of\nhaving Col. Calvin Goddard\ndemonstrtae his ballistic expert\nness before the Baker case jury\nwould be carried out.\nThe proposal made by Mr. Col\nlins, which was hastily accepted\nby the defense yesterday, called\nfor a test of Colonel Goddard\u2019s\nability to trace certain bullets to\ncertain guns. /It was proposed\nto have the ballistic expert fire\nbullets from seven to ten re\nvolvers in the presence of the\njury and then to trace the bullets\nback to the revolvers by mark-\nIngs on the bullets.\nCounter Proposal\nCharles Henry Smith, chief de\nfense counsel for Campbell, pro\nposed that bullets be fired from\nthe supposed death gun only, and\nthen tests would be made on\nthem by Dr. Albert Hamilton, de\nfense firearms expert, co prove\nthat the bullets did not corre\nspond with the lethal ones.\nThen Colonel Goddard would\nmake tests in an effort to prove\nthat these tests bullets were simi\nlar to the ones taken from the\nslain girl\u2019s body.\nMr. Collins was waiting to hear\n'formally from the defense iday.\nIn his office were Colonel God\ndard and Lieut. John Fowler gun\nexpert of the local Police Depart\nment.\nReady for Task\nAsked what he thought of the\nlatest move of Mr. Smith, Colonel\nGoddard said:\n\u201cI cannot see how it would\nbe pertinent to the case. We\nhave made tests with the al\nleged death gun and I can\nprove that the bullets corre\nspond with the mortal ones.\n\u201cI am ready to make tests,\nin accordance with the wishes\nof Mr. Collins, with any num\nber of guns, so as to prove con\nclusively that ballistics is an\naccurate test and a recognized\nscience.\u201d\nIt is not known just when or\nwhere the tests are to be made.\nMr. Collins indicated that tests\n(Continued on Page 2, Col. 6)\nOfficial Race Program\nToday at Laurel\nWeather Clear; Track Fast\nFIRST RACE\nOne Mile\n5445\u2014Golden Rock (Cooper) 105\n5440\u2014 Eilona (Kennedy) 104\n5445\u2014Jake Jacoby (Godfrey) 105\n5444\u2014Wandering Flower (Madely).. 109\n5441\u2014 Queen City (No boy) 100\n5443\u2014Bright Quality (No boy) 100\n5443\u2014Bright Dav (E. Smith) io\n5441\u2014 Wild Fowl (Renick) 100\n5442\u2014 Mullah (No boy) 103\nSECOND RACE\nOne Mlle\n5452\u2014 Jolly King (Workman) 114\n5459\u2014Astrakhan (Rossi) 110\n5459\u2014Play Bird (Quackenbushs 105\n5450\u2014 Tommy Boy (Coltiletti) 117\n5457\u2014 Kensington (Leishman) 107\n5459\u2014 Ultra Marine (Riley) 105\n5453\u2014 Burgoo (Renick) 10S\n5458\u2014 Dunfern (Robertson) 110\n5455\u2014 Sir Byron (Cannon) 10S\n5451\u2014 Portcodine (Thibodeaux) 113\n5454\u2014 Catty (Wells) 103\n5456\u2014 Prince Peter (Watters) 108\nTHIRD RACE\nThree-Quarters Mile\n5460\u2014 Balko (J. Bejshak) 126\n5466 \u2014Aymond (Meade) 90\n5460\u2014 The Heathen (Coltiletti) 126\n5461\u2014 Jock (No boy) 114\n5463 Polydor (Ellis) 122\n5465\u2014Morsel (Riley) 95\n5464\u2014 Maya (Leishmnn) 114\n5463\u2014Colossal (No boy) 10S\nFOURTH RACE\nOne Mi r\n5457\u2014 Scotte (Bejshak) 114\n5475 Dark Magnet (Coltiletti) 109\n5476\u2014 Friaress (Lelshmun) 111\n5475\u2014Dark Edwina (Robertson) 11l\n5470\u2014Risque (Steffeni 117\n5479\u2014Magothy (Howell) 117\n64*\u2014Ontburat (Wuuri) 111\nCLERGY \u00abS\n0. 0. \u2018BUY NOW\u2019\nCAMPAIGN\nBishops Freeman, McDowell\nand Washington Pastors\nLaud C of C. on Movement\n\u201cEvery good citizen should\ngive his support to such a wise\nand practical program as out\nlined in the \u2018Buy Now\u2019 cam\npaign launched by the Wash\nington Chamber of Commerce.\n\u201cWe can not face a hard\nwinter without doing every\nthing we can to relieve the\nsituation in all quarters. We\nshould not try to do this by\ncharity, but strike out in other\ndirections, such as wise and\nprompt buying.\u201d\nWith these words, the Rev.\nWilliam F. McDowell, Methodist\nBishop of Washington, today\nstruck the keynote of the Wash\nington clergy\u2019s reaction to the\ndrive started yesterday by ttie\nChamber of Commerce to relieve\nbusiness depression current here.\nThe Chamber has issued a call\nto the clergy, press and other\ncivic groups in the city to rally\nto its new slogan and to assist\nin building up'a buying program\nthat will rejuvenate business here.\nBishop McDowell was followed\nclosely in his support of the\ndrive by nearly all influential\nchurch men in the city, whose\nexpressions follow\nThe Rev. James E. Freeman,\nEpiscopal Bishop of Washington:\n\u201cI think it is an excellent\nidea. I am heartily in favor of\nsuch a campaign. But I also\nsuggest that, although we con\ncentrate on starting such a\nmovement at this time, we\nmake it a continuing condi\ntion and keep on buying instead\nof makirfc just a superficial\nspurt.\u201d\nThe Rev. Earle Wilfley, pastor\nof the National City Christian\nChurch:\n\u201cThis campaign is indeed a\ngood sugestion. I think it is\na move in the right direction\nand that we should keep money\nin circulation. The Chamber\nof Commerce should be com\nmended for its efforts to get\npeople to do what they can do\nto relieve the present business\ndepression in this city.\u201d\nThe Rev. Dr. Joseph R. Sizoo,\npastor of the New York Avenue\nPresbyterian Church:\n\u201cAny movement whatsoever\nwhich is going to lift the bur\n(Continued on Page 2, Col. 2)\n5474\u2014Tambour (Schaefer) 11l\n5471\u2014 Baba Kenny (Renick) 119\n5473\u2014Buckup (Garner) 11l\n5472\u2014 Blind Lane (Walls) lls>\nFIFTH RACE\nMile and one-quarter\n5481\u2014 Mr. Sponge (Garner) 115\n5437\u2014Maya (No boy).. 106\n5489\u2014Wcodcraft (No boy) 108\n5488\u2014 Ned O. (Robertson) 113\n5483\u2014 Starpatic (Catrone) 120\n54S7\u2014Conclave (Leishman) 112\n5482 Spinach (Ellis) 126\n5489\u2014 Porphyry (Meade) 90\n5486\u2014 Her Grace (Watters) 108\n5487\u2014 Nile Maiden (Leishman) 102\n5489\u2014Sun Falcon (Bejshak) 105\n5484\u2014 Erin (W. Carroll) 10S\n5480\u2014Questionnaire (Workman).... 119\n5485\u2014 Valencinnes (Steffen) 10S\n5489\u2014Rock Glare (No boy) 95\n5489\u2014 Jim Dandy (Baker) 112\nSIXTH RACE\nMile and one-sixteenth\n\u25a0s494\u2014Fair Thorn (W'ells) 104\n5490\u2014 Come On (Day) 109\n5499\u2014stern Chaser (Tilden) 109\n5493 \u2014Red Cliffe (Palumbo) 114\n5499\u2014Rockslide (Harvey) 112\n6495\u2014Raucona (Louman) 109\n5496\u2014 stephanite (Robertson) 110\n5492\u2014Make Haste (M. Garner) 112\n5498\u2014 Wayfarer (Leishman) 108\n5499\u2014 Union Central (.Watters) 112\n5497\u2014 Amsterdam (Riley) 112\n5491 Ruby Keller (No toy; 11l\nSEVENTH RACE\nMlle and one-quarter\n5503\u2014 Naylor (W. Day) 103\n5504\u2014 Wrackell (Quackenbush in)\n6506 \u2014Honey Grove (No b\u00aby) 163\n5501\u2014 Butter John (Louman) 112\n5502\u2014 Replevin (Garner) 114\n5500\u2014 Spanish (Workman).. 112\n66\u00ab\u00bb\u2014Maha Bailee* (Walla) mm 1U\nSATURDAY, OCTOBER 25, 1930\nPrincess Becomes Boris* Queen\nA MBh.\nflk W\nw I\ns K Wl Uh.\nJ W\u201d 11\nW- A\njBhE\nMB\n\u25a0g| |Wj v B\nI B B\nI\nvfcu v w* B\nWil Lgs?- M\nwlil 1\n\u2014lnternational Newsreel\nPRINCESS GIOVANNA KING BORIS\nPRINCESS GIOVANNA, daughter of the king and queen of Italy, today became the\nbride of King Boris of Bulgaria.\nBORIS WEDS AS\nSTORM RAGES\nASSISI, Italy, Oct. 25 (IJJ.S.).\nBeneath the beautiful frescoed\ndome of the ancient Church of\nSt. Francis, Princess Giovanna of\nItaly became the world\u2019s youngest\nQueen today as the wife of King\nBoris HI of Bulgaria.\nDespite the wishes of all to have\nthe ceremony 1 simple in the ex\nextreme, the presence of the en\ntire Italian and'Bulgarian royal\nfamilies, the women in flowing\ngowns and the men in magnificent\nuniforms, was sufficient to make\nthe ceremony a thing of impres\nsive splendor.\nThe religious ceremony was per\nformed by Father Risso, custo\ndian of the Franciscan community\nand rector of the ancient church,\nbuilt in the year 1228.\nStorm Strikes City\nA terrific storm broke over\nAssisi just as the last group in\nthe bridal prpeession entered the\nchurch.\nThe silks and satins of royalty\nbarely escaped the drivng rain,\nwind and hail which swept with\nwhistling force 'from the snow\ncovered heights. The squall raged\nalmost throughout the church\nceremony.\nThe enormous crowds which\npressed in solid ranks about the\nchurch entrance refused to budge,\n(Continued on Page 2, Col. 1)\nTHE WASHINGTON\nChurch Reporter\n\npresenting news\nand activities of the\nsocial and religious\nwork of Washington\nchurches during the\npast and coming week\nappears today in\u2014\nvOffiBMWES\nPage 7\nn \u00aba,\nFrench Honor\nLindy and\nCoste\nPARIS, Oct. 25 (IN.S.) .\u2014Ele\nvation of Col. Charles A. Lind\nbergh to the rank of commander\nof the French Legion of Honor\nwas announced by President\nGaston Doumergue today as he\nconferred the same honor on\nMajor Dieudonne Coste, French\nairman just returned to France\nafter his flight from Paris to\nNew York.\nAs President Doumergue was\npinning the insignia upon Major\nCoste\u2019s lapel, he announced he\nhad just signed a decree making\nColonel Lindbergh a commander\nalso.\nMajor Coste arrived at Le\nBourget Field this afternoon from\nHavre, where he disembarked yes\nterday.\nTbifoy's Grid Line-Up\nDICKINSON GEO. WASH.\n5 Williams Left End Sturtevant 29\n14 Bonney Left Tackle Chestnut 48\n22 Hilddbberger Left Guard Sommers 43\n20 LaVanture Center Chambers 49\n1 Eichorn Right Guard Demas 52\n17 Shomock Right Tackle Wilson 44\n8 Brillhart Right End Mulvey 32\n16 Foley Quarterback Carter 30\n10 J. Myers Left Halfback Carlin 21\n2 Lipinski Right Halfback Kriemelmeyer 36\n13 L- Casner Fullback Bagranoff 45\nDICKINSON\u2014C. Myers (3), Sloan (4), E. Casner (6), Etter\n(7), Green (9), Forcey (11), Spahr (12), Weidner (15), Dough\nerty (18), Jenkins (19), Lehman (21), Budowski, Colburn, Cook,\nDavidson, Kennedy, Hartshorn, Johnson, Reeves, Vivadelli.\nGEORGE WASHINGTON\u2014Lannon (16), H. Jones (23), Mc-\nGrew (24), Wells (25), Helvestine (26), Fenlon (27), Berko\nwitz (28), Rielly (31), Eakers (33), Hale (34), Max Brown\n(35), Duffalo (41), Hoffman (42), Galloway (46), McQueen\n(47), O\u2019Brien (50), Johnson (51).\nReferee, C. R. McClure (Georgetown); umpire, Edward\nTowers (Columbia); head linesman, Charles Guyon (Carlisle).\nTHREE CENTS\nG. W. U. POINTED\nFOR DIMOON\nWhat is thought to be a breath\ning spell in George Washington\u2019s\nstrenuous football schedule will be\noffered today when Dickinson Col\nlege eleven, of Carlisle, Pa\u201e is met\nat Clark Griffith Stadium. The\nkick-off is due at 2:30 o\u2019clock.\nThis is the only strictly local col\nlege game of the day.\nThe Colonials, supervised by\nLeonard Walsh, are favored\nto turn back the ponderous\nmachine that checked them\nby a 7-to-6 margin a year ago.\nWalsh is pinch-hitting for Ath\nletic Director Jim Pixlee, who is\nspeeding toward Tulsa. Okla., to\nscout the Tulsa University team\nin its meeting with Phillips Col\nlege tonight.\nA capable attack and markedly\nimproved defense will be uncov\nered by the Colonials when play\ngets under way. Many of the\n(Continued on Page 9, Col. J)\nEDITION\nDISCOVERED\nIN RAIDS\nON REDS\nAssassination Attempt Was\nScheduled to Take Place at\nthe Opening of Parliament\nVIENNA, Oct. 25 (INs.).\u2014Dis\ncovery of a plot to assassinate\nKing Carol of Rumania and\nblow up the royal palace in\nBucharest was announced by the\nRumanian police today, according\nto reports received here from\nBucharest.\nThe assassination attempt was\nscheduled to take place at the\nopening of the Rumanian Par\nliament, the reports stated.\nThe plot was said to have\nbeen unearthed during a series\nof raids directed against an al\nlege pro-Soviet espionage system\nresulting in more than 100 ar\nrests.\n20 om>\nSHELLS SHIP\nBERLIN, Oct. 25 (I.NJ3J.\nTwenty persons were killed and\n35 injured when the Hamburg-\nAmerican Line steamer Baden was\nshelled by Fort Chaopachana,\nnear Rio de Janeiro, according to\na message received bj the Ger\nman Foreign Office from its min\nister to Brazil today.\nThe Foreign Office was advised\nthe Baden was struck as it was\nleaving the harbor of Rio de\nJaneiro, bound for Buenos Aires.\nAmong the victims, the message\ndeclared, were former members of\nthe deposed government of Presi\ndent Washington Luis, who were\nattempting to escape aboard the\nBaden following rebel seizure of\nthe capital.\nThe German government im\nmediately wirelessed its represen\ntatives for more detailed informa\ntion. According to reports here,\nthe majority of the passengers\naboard the Baden were Spanish\nimmigrants bound for the Argen\ntine.\nThe master of the Baden re\nported the incident to the head\noffice of the Hamburg-American\nLine at Hamburg, stating the\nBaden immediately returned to\nport with her flag at half mast.\nIt was reported the shot had\nbeen fired merely as a warning,\nbut accidentally struck the vessel.\nAccording to word received\nhere, the Brazilian ministry of\n(Continued on Page 2, Col. 3)\nPaddock Picks Five\nWinners At Laurel\nThe Washington Times\nhandicapper, \u201cP add o c k,\u201d\nmade the fans forget all\nabout the cold at the track\nyesterday when he slammed\nover five winners out of\nseven races.\nHe started off the day in\nthe first race with Brains,\nthen came back with Ivory\n2nd in the jumping event. In\nthe third race his picking\nran out but in the fourth\nrace Gerard finished second.\nHe then hit his stride by\npicking Avalon, winner of\nthe feature race, and swelled\nthe fans* pocketbooks in the\nsixth rac? when he picked\nFrumper, paying $24.90, the\nlongest price wniner of the\nday.\nHe finished out the card\nby picking My Scoop in the\nnightcap.\nHis selections appear each\nday in th mid-day scratches\nedition and Home Edition,\ntogether with scratches at\nall tracks.","height":"30608","width":"24445"}}
